  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some ways you can get into Johns Hopkins University?",
  "response": "Getting into Johns Hopkins University, one of the leading research institutions in the United States, requires careful planning and a strong application. Here are several steps and strategies to increase your chances of admission:\n\n1. **Academic Excellence**: \n   - Maintain a high GPA throughout high school, focusing on a rigorous course load that includes Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate (IB), or honors courses.\n   - Aim for strong standardized test scores (if submitting). While Johns Hopkins is test-optional for some applicants, competitive scores on the SAT or ACT can still bolster your application.\n\n2. **Extracurricular Involvement**: \n   - Engage in meaningful extracurricular activities, including clubs, sports, or community service, especially those related to your intended field of study.\n   - Take on leadership roles to demonstrate your ability to contribute to the campus community.\n\n3. **Personal Statement and Essays**: \n   - Write compelling personal essays that reflect your interests, passions, and experiences. Show how these relate to your desire to attend Johns Hopkins.\n   - Be authentic; admissions officers appreciate genuine reflections and insights.\n\n4. **Letters of Recommendation**: \n   - Obtain strong letters of recommendation from teachers or mentors who know you well and can speak to your strengths, character, and potential.\n   - Choose recommenders who can provide specific examples of your achievements and contributions.\n\n5. **Interviews**: \n   - Participate in an optional interview (if available) to further discuss your interests and fit for the university. It\u2019s a chance to add a personal touch to your application.\n\n6. **Research and Fit**: \n   - Investigate Johns Hopkins' programs, faculty, and unique opportunities (like research, internships, etc.) to explain why you\u2019re a good fit for the university.\n   - Tailor your application materials to reflect your knowledge of the university\u2019s values and offerings.\n\n7. **Demonstrated Interest**: \n   - Engage with the university through campus visits, information sessions, or virtual events. This can help demonstrate your interest in attending Johns Hopkins.\n\n8. **Financial Aid and Scholarships**: \n   - If needed, explore financial aid options and apply for scholarships. Understanding the financial aspects of attendance can help you plan better.\n\n9. **Apply Early**: \n   - Consider applying early decision if you are sure that Johns Hopkins is your first choice. This can increase your chances of acceptance, though it is a binding commitment.\n\n10. **Stay Informed**: \n   - Keep up-to-date with any changes in application procedures or requirements from Johns Hopkins, as these can vary from year to year.\n\nRemember that admission to competitive universities like Johns Hopkins is holistic, meaning they consider various aspects of your application. Showcasing your authentic self and demonstrating how you will contribute to the university community can make a significant difference.",
